fix(scheduler): checkout window uses rolling time threshold instead of end-date

Root cause: CheckOutScheduler opened checkout based on endDate <= today
(date-only), with a day-keyed idempotency lock. This meant checkout could
open at midnight instead of ~1 hour before the actual trip end time.

Changes:
- CheckOutScheduler: compute thresholdTime = now + windowHoursBeforeTrip,
  query by endTime <= thresholdTime instead of endDate <= today
- Idempotency key now uses hour + 15-minute bucket (matching check-in
  scheduler) with 14-minute TTL for 15-minute cron compatibility
- CheckOutService.findBookingsForCheckoutOpening(LocalDateTime) delegates
  to BookingRepository.findBookingsForCheckoutWindowOpening(thresholdTime)
- application-dev.properties: added checkout scheduler config section
- application-prod.properties: added env-overridable
  CHECKOUT_WINDOW_HOURS_BEFORE_TRIP and CHECKOUT_LATE_GRACE_MINUTES
